8832.t:
[§321-34]  Cytomegalovirus public education.
(a)  The department of health shall provide public education to inform pregnant
women and women who may become pregnant regarding:

     (1)  The transmission of the cytomegalovirus to pregnant
women and women who may become pregnant;

     (2)  Birth defects caused by congenital cytomegalovirus;

     (3)  Methods of diagnosing congenital cytomegalovirus;
and

     (4)  Available preventative measures.

     (b)  The department of health shall provide the
information described in subsection (a) to:

     (1)  Hospitals licensed pursuant to section 321-14.5;

     (2)  Health care providers offering care to pregnant women
and infants;

     (3)  Registered family child care homes;

     (4)  Licensed group child care centers;

     (5)  Licensed group child care homes;

     (6)  Licensed infant and toddler child care centers; and

     (7)  Religious, ecclesiastical, or denominational organizations
offering children's programs as a part of worship services. [L 2015, c 232, §1]

